<subSubSection id="C3776556ED213847FF78F89FFBE5F99A" lastPageId="626" lastPageNumber="627" pageId="624" pageNumber="625" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED213845FF78F89FFBDEF95E" blockId="624.[136,778,1635,2070]" lastBlockId="624.[810,1452,1295,2070]" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED213845FF78F89FFE24F8AA" bold="true" box="[189,481,1873,1899]" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FDA5F89CFD15F8AD" box="[608,720,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423</figureCitation>
A-C) vermiform; body length 4.70-5.09 mm; body length of dissected specimen (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FEBCF858FE34F871" box="[377,497,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423B</figureCitation>
) 4.72 mm. Body width variable, narrow in non-ovigerous young adult (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FD19F876FF0EF835" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423A</figureCitation>
), 1.19 mm in dissected ovigerous specimen (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FD19F814FF0CF7D7" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423B</figureCitation>
), and muchwider, 1.80 mm, infemalewithexpanded brood pouch containing nauplii. Prosome divisible by constrictionintocephalosomeandmetasome:cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FCF7FA9DFC06FAAF" box="[818,963,1363,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423D, E</figureCitation>
) much narrower than metasome. Metasome divisible into short, narrower anterior part (possibly repesenting first pedigerous somite) and longer, broader remaining part. Metasome of expanded specimen (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FABBFA77FCADFA37" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423C</figureCitation>
) with 2 constrictions. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FAEBFA15FA66FA37" box="[1326,1443,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423F</figureCitation>
) small, graduallynarrowing posteriorly; consistingof short genital somite bearing copulatory pore on ventral surface and unsegmented abdomen, wider than long (260×320 μ). Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FC2FF9ADFB8CF9BF" box="[1002,1097,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423</figureCitation>
G-I) vestigial, bearing 5 minute setae of variable size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED213845FC9AF966FAECF7D7" blockId="624.[810,1452,1295,2070]" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FC14F969FB82F903" box="[977,1095,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423D</figureCitation>
) broadened distally. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FCF7F907FC64F925" box="[818,929,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423J</figureCitation>
) lobate, aslongas wide, unsegmented, with indentation subdistally on dorsal margin, apparently unarmed, but ornamented with many short, thick setules on distal region. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED213845FBB8F8FEFB39F88B" box="[1149,1276,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="624" pageNumber="625">Fig. 423K</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented, consistingof unarmed coxa and basis and unsegmented endopod; endopod distinctly narrower than proximal segments, about 3.1 timeslongerthan wide (80×26 μm), with minute spinules on margins: armed with 7 small setae (1 subdistal and 6 distal) plus short terminal claw, one-thirdaslongas endopod, almost straight.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED203844FF4DF8BDFCA1F835" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="625" pageNumber="626" startId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" targetPageId="625">
