</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
