<paragraph id="8BD236DDED233847FF78FA59FBB7F9D9" blockId="626.[136,778,1431,2071]" lastBlockId="626.[810,1452,1431,1729]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">
Mouthparts positioned deep inside pre-oral cavity formed by anterior and posterior folds on ventral side of cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FEE8FA15FE63FA37" box="[301,422,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 423" captionStartId="625.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[213,1350,209,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-17@625.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="625" captionText="FIGURE 423. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus of young adult, dorsal; B, habitus of ovigerous adult, dorsal; C, habitus of expanded adult containing nauplii, dorsal; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, anterior part of prosome, left; F, urosome, ventral; G, H, I, caudal rami; J, antennule; K, antenna. Scale bars: A–C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.2 mm; F, 0.1 mm; G–I, 0.02 mm; J, K, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592166/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 423D</figureCitation>
). Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FDE2FA15FD5AFA37" box="[551,671,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424A</figureCitation>
) smooth, unornamented, with broadly convex posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FEC3F9D1FE65F9FB" box="[262,416,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424B, C</figureCitation>
) consisting coxa and biramous palp: coxa (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FED3F98FFE48F99D" box="[278,397,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424C</figureCitation>
) with broad gnathobase bearing 1 acutely pointed and 3 blunt teeth along distal third of medial margin and with remaining part of medial margin pectinate (spinulose); palp (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FE7FF969FDEEF903" box="[442,555,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424B</figureCitation>
) consistingof basis, 2-segmented exopod, and unsegmented endopod; basis with 1 setaat mediodistal corner; exopod small, armed with 2 setae on each segment; endopod much larger than exopod, armed with 5 setae; setae on palp broad, but feebly pinnate. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FE22F89CFD9BF8AD" box="[487,606,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424D</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, lobate, bearing 9 broad setae: 2 setae on medial margin, 4 leaf-like setae on distal margin, and 3 setaeon outer margin. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FE95F876FE01F813" box="[336,452,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424E</figureCitation>
) 2-segmented; first segment (syncoxa) bearing 2 setae medially; secondsegment (basis + endopod) bearing 4 setae (1 largeand 3 small) medially and bilobed distal part; each distal lobe tipped with 1 small spinule. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED233847FB15FA77FA8CFA15" box="[1232,1353,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 424" captionStartId="626.[136,245,1295,1321]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@626.[136,1451,167,1262]" captionTargetPageId="626" captionText="FIGURE 424. Phyllodelphys capensis gen. et sp. nov., female. A, labrum; B, mandibular palp; C, mandibular gnathobase; D, maxillule; E, maxilla; F, maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592168/files/figure.png" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Fig. 424F</figureCitation>
) lobate, bearing 4 leaf-like setae of different sizes, 2 larger distal and 2 smaller subdistal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED233847FC9AF9EEFC29F9F8" blockId="626.[810,1452,1431,1729]" box="[863,1004,1567,1594]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Legs absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED233847FC9AF98CFBE5F99A" blockId="626.[810,1452,1431,1729]" box="[863,1056,1601,1628]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED233847FC9AF98CFC59F99D" bold="true" box="[863,924,1602,1628]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED233847FC9AF9AAFC5FF900" pageId="626" pageNumber="627" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED233847FC9AF9AAFC5FF900" blockId="626.[810,1452,1431,1729]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED233847FC9AF9AAFC09F9BF" bold="true" box="[863,972,1636,1662]" pageId="626" pageNumber="627">Remarks</emphasis>
.Thefunctionalsignificanceoftheflattened, leaf-like setae found on the maxillule and maxilliped is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
